<h2>Wizard (Flow Progress)</h2>
<p>The reference <strong>Flow-Progress</strong> surface — a <code>&lt;wizard-flow&gt;</code> custom element that renders <strong>where a user is</strong> in a multi-step workflow and <strong>each step's status</strong>. It is the UX member of the <a href="/projects/webworkflows/">Web Workflows</a> protocol and the canonical <code>register: wizard</code> realization of the <a href="/intents/flow-progress/">Flow Progress Intent</a>.</p>

<p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
  <strong>Status:</strong> active — <code>WizardElement</code> wires a portable workflow graph through the swappable <code>customWorkflowEngine</code> (<a href="/backlog/634-meta-intent-workflow-as-composable-intent/">#634</a> / <a href="/backlog/650-native-workflow-engine/">#650</a>) and renders the position + per-step status. Slice A of <a href="/backlog/651-reference-wizard-block-composing-the-flow-progress-intent-we/">#651</a>.
</p>

<h3>Owns nothing it can compose</h3>
<p>The wizard owns no orchestration — transitions, guards, parallel, and completion stay on the engine (the protocol). It composes the rest:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/blocks/stepper/">Stepper</a> — the linear-presentation mechanics it already owns: <code>aria-current="step"</code>, the "Step N of M" live announcement, and one-panel-at-a-time switching. The stepper runs in <code>free</code> progression here because the <strong>engine</strong> is the source of truth for position — the stepper reflects it, it does not gate it.</li>
  <li><a href="/blocks/workflow-engine/">Workflow Engine</a> — the running instance. Next sends an event (<code>NEXT</code> by default); Back calls the instance's <code>back()</code>; the engine's <code>onTransition</code> stream is mapped to per-step status.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Flow Progress Intent dimensions</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Value</th><th>Why</th></tr>
  <tr><td><code>register</code></td><td><code>wizard</code></td><td>The dedicated-surface flow — the most-permissive default register</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>stepStatus</code></td><td><code>wait</code> / <code>process</code> / <code>finish</code> / <code>error</code></td><td>Derived per step from the engine position (index-based) with <code>error</code> read from the threaded context, surfaced as <code>data-step-status</code> on each indicator</td></tr>
  <tr><td><code>movement</code></td><td><code>back-allowed</code></td><td>Back/undo via the instance's <code>back()</code> — the most-permissive default</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Droppable</h3>
<p>Set <code>.graph</code> (and optionally <code>.options</code> for an engine name, the Next event type, or per-step labels) on a <code>&lt;wizard-flow&gt;</code> element. Author per-step content with <code>&lt;template data-step-id="…"&gt;</code> children; absent that, each panel renders its step label. Proven by its render test (current position, per-step status mapping, back/undo, error surfacing).</p>
